# MCP Server Documentation Guidelines

## README.md Structure

1. Brief Description
   - One-line description of the server's purpose
   - Key features in bullet points (max 5)

2. Installation
   - NPM installation command
   - MCP configuration JSON snippet
   - Required environment variables explanation

3. Available Tools
   - List each tool with:
     - Name and brief description
     - Input schema in TypeScript/JSON
     - Basic usage example

4. Basic Configuration
   - Essential environment variables
   - Common configuration options
   - Default values

## CONTRIBUTING.md Structure

1. Development Setup
   - Repository cloning
   - Dependencies installation
   - Build instructions
   - Test commands

2. Project Structure
   - Directory layout
   - Key files explanation
   - Architecture overview

3. Development Guidelines
   - Code style
   - Git conventions
   - Testing requirements
   - Documentation requirements

4. Detailed Features
   - In-depth feature explanations
   - Implementation details
   - Performance considerations
   - Error handling approach

5. API Documentation
   - Detailed API endpoints
   - Response formats
   - Error codes
   - Rate limiting details

## General Rules

1. README.md
   - Focus on installation and basic usage
   - Keep it concise and user-focused
   - Include only essential configuration
   - Use clear code examples
   - Avoid implementation details

2. CONTRIBUTING.md
   - Include all development details
   - Provide comprehensive documentation
   - Include architectural decisions
   - Document internal workings
   - Include troubleshooting guides

3. Documentation Style
   - Use consistent formatting
   - Include TypeScript types
   - Provide working code examples
   - Document error scenarios
   - Keep examples up to date
